reviews.review_text: Fun in the wind and sun I was at this show....what a blast.  Sunny windy hillside at the top of the pass over the Sierras.  Hoses spraying down the crowd, wind blowing the sound around, sometimes it sounded great, sometimes not.  Everyone in a great mood, just dancing with the dust flying and the good vibes pouring out.  How was the show?  lol...not sure.  Pretty average, sloppy, forgetting words, running through some songs.  No one cared.  The Grateful Dead showed up to spread peace love and happiness to the crowd, and succeeded as usual. Awesome parking lot scene to boot!  I'm not a picky deadhead, just loved loved loved this day.
